HEADWORD: Madding
<hw>Mad"ding</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Affected with
madness; raging; furious.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Mad"ding*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos> <mark>[Archaic]</mark></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Far from the <qex>madding</qex> crowd's ignoble strife.</q>
<rj><qau>Gray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>madding</qex> wheels⟦br⟧
Of brazen chariots raged.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maddish</ent>⟦br⟧
